# Deterministic line endings across machines.
#
# Root cause this guards against: core.autocrlf=true on Windows checkouts rewrites
# repo-LF files to CRLF in the working tree. Files that execute INSIDE Linux
# containers must stay LF — a CRLF entrypoint.sh makes tini fail shebang resolution
# and the migrator container exits 7. These rules override autocrlf for those files.

# Baseline: let Git normalize text to LF in the repo, native EOL in the working tree.
* text=auto

# --- Files that run inside Linux containers: force LF regardless of core.autocrlf ---
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.bash          text eol=lf
Dockerfile      text eol=lf
Dockerfile.*    text eol=lf
*.dockerignore  text eol=lf
*.conf          text eol=lf

# --- Binary assets: never touch EOL or attempt text diffs ---
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.ico   binary
*.gz    binary
*.zip   binary
